Nevehir Kapadokya Airport (IATA: NAV,ICAO: LTAZ) is an airport 30 km (19 mi) from Nevehir, Turkey, opened in 1998. Airport's domestic and international passenger terminal covers an area of 3,500 m and has a parking lot for 400 cars. In 2006, the airport served 392 cargo, 833 passenger aircraft and 27,832 passengers.[1]
